---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageIntro from '../components/PageIntro.astro';

// League policies, transcribed from Stacey's Weather and Cancellation policy
// docs (2026-07-03). Substance preserved as written; normalizations applied
// per the design spec: official email everywhere, the Lessons "after 24 hours"
// typo corrected to "within", no em dashes, brand-green hearts.
const EMAIL = 'ladiesonthelinks.league@gmail.com';
const FACEBOOK_URL = 'https://www.facebook.com/Ladiesonthelinksgolfleague/';
const BOOKWHEN_URL = 'https://bookwhen.com/ladiesonthelinks';
---

<Layout
  title="Policies · Ladies on the Links"
  description="Weather and cancellation policies for the Ladies on the Links women's golf league at North Hill Country Club in Duxbury, MA."
>
  <PageIntro
    eyebrow="The fine print, with love"
    title="League policies"
    lede="How we handle weather calls and booking cancellations. For the quick version, see the quick answers on the Contact page."
  />

  <!-- Weather policy -->
  <section id="weather" class="mx-auto max-w-2xl scroll-mt-24 px-6 pb-16">
    <div class="space-y-5 leading-relaxed text-slate reveal">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-light text-forest">Weather policy</h2>

      <h3 class="pt-2 font-serif text-xl text-forest">Our philosophy</h3>
      <p>
        <strong class="font-medium text-forest">We play in the rain.</strong> Golf is an outdoor sport, and a little
        drizzle is part of the game. That said, we will never ask you to play in unsafe conditions. Lightning, severe
        storms, or truly unplayable weather are a different story. Our goal is to give you as much notice as possible
        while still enjoying every Monday we can.
      </p>

      <h3 class="pt-2 font-serif text-xl text-forest">League play: when we cancel</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
        <li>
          League play is cancelled only if conditions are dangerous: lightning, severe thunderstorms, or course closure
          by North Hill Country Club.
        </li>
        <li>Light or steady rain alone is not a cancellation. People play golf in the rain, and we will too.</li>
        <li>
          The final call is made by our pro, <strong class="font-medium text-forest">Christian Grace</strong>, in
          coordination with North Hill Country Club. His decision is final.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="pt-2 font-serif text-xl text-forest">How and when you will hear from us</h3>
      <p>We know last-minute calls are stressful. Here is our commitment to you:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
        <li>
          <strong class="font-medium text-forest">Decision deadline:</strong> a go or no-go decision will be
          communicated no later than 1 hour before your scheduled tee time.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="font-medium text-forest">Where to look:</strong> all weather updates are sent by league email
          and posted to our
          <a href={FACEBOOK_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-medium text-rose underline-offset-4 hover:underline">Facebook page</a>.
          These are the only official channels, so there is no need to check anywhere else.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="font-medium text-forest">What if it changes after you have left?</strong> Christian will make
          the call at the course if conditions deteriorate after play begins.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="pt-2 font-serif text-xl text-forest">Clinics and lessons</h3>
      <p>
        Clinics have a lower threshold for cancellation. We want beginners and developing players to have the best
        possible learning experience, and rain makes that harder. If your clinic is cancelled:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
        <li>You will be offered a makeup slot.</li>
        <li>
          If neither makeup date works for you, please email us at
          <a href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`} class="font-medium text-rose underline-offset-4 hover:underline">{EMAIL}</a>
          and we will find a solution.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="pt-2 font-serif text-xl text-forest">Refunds and makeup sessions</h3>
      <p>We do not offer cash refunds for weather-related cancellations. Here is what we do offer:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
        <li>
          <strong class="font-medium text-forest">League play cancelled by the club:</strong> you receive credit toward
          a future session or a designated makeup date.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="font-medium text-forest">League play proceeds but you choose not to play:</strong> no refund
          or credit is issued. We understand, everyone has their limit! But we cannot hold spots for weather-preference
          opt-outs.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="font-medium text-forest">Clinic or tee times cancelled by the club:</strong> full makeup
          session offered at no additional cost.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>We will always do right by our members. If something feels off, reach out to us directly.</p>

      <h3 class="pt-2 font-serif text-xl text-forest">What to bring on a rainy day</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
        <li>Rain jacket or poncho (golf-specific ones let you swing freely)</li>
        <li>Extra golf gloves, wet grips are slippery</li>
        <li>Waterproof golf shoes or extra socks</li>
        <li>A good attitude. Some of the best rounds happen in the rain 💚</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Diamond divider (accent motif shared with Home). -->
  <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-xs items-center gap-4 px-6 pb-16" aria-hidden="true">
    <span class="rule flex-1"></span>
    <span class="h-1.5 w-1.5 rotate-45 bg-rose"></span>
    <span class="rule flex-1"></span>
  </div>

  <!-- Cancellation policy -->
  <section id="cancellation" class="mx-auto max-w-2xl scroll-mt-24 px-6 pb-16">
    <div class="space-y-5 leading-relaxed text-slate reveal">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-light text-forest">Cancellation policy</h2>
      <p class="text-sm tracking-wide text-rose">Tee times, lessons, and clinics</p>

      <p>
        <strong class="font-medium text-forest">Book your spot, and you have 24 hours to cancel. After that, you are
        locked in.</strong> Your booking holds your spot and supports the league so we keep all of our designated tee
        times, so please book with intention. We would love to see you every Monday, or as often as you can commit!
        🏌️‍♀️💚
      </p>

      <h3 class="pt-2 font-serif text-xl text-forest">League tee times</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
        <li>
          <strong class="font-medium text-forest">Within 24 hours of booking:</strong> cancel directly through your
          Bookwhen confirmation email. Your spot is automatically released to the waitlist.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="font-medium text-forest">No-shows:</strong> if you do not show and do not reach out, your spot
          is forfeited and cannot be offered to anyone on the waitlist. For this reason, we ask you to cancel whenever
          possible.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="pt-2 font-serif text-xl text-forest">Lessons and clinics</h3>
      <p>The same 24-hour policy applies to all lessons and clinics booked through Ladies on the Links:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
        <li>
          <strong class="font-medium text-forest">Within 24 hours of booking:</strong> cancel through your booking
          confirmation. Your spot is released to others on the waitlist.
        </li>
        <li><strong class="font-medium text-forest">No-shows:</strong> your session is forfeited.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="pt-2 font-serif text-xl text-forest">How to cancel</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
        <li>
          <strong class="font-medium text-forest">Through Bookwhen:</strong> open your original booking confirmation
          email and click the cancellation link. This is the fastest way and automatically opens your spot.
        </li>
        <li><strong class="font-medium text-forest">Text Stacey:</strong> for clarification or anything urgent.</li>
        <li>
          <strong class="font-medium text-forest">Email:</strong>
          <a href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`} class="font-medium text-rose underline-offset-4 hover:underline">{EMAIL}</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Please do not cancel by posting on Facebook or by DM on social media. Those messages can be missed. Text or
        email is always the right move.
      </p>

      <h3 class="pt-2 font-serif text-xl text-forest">Want to swap your tee time?</h3>
      <p>
        If you need to move to a different time slot rather than cancel outright, Bookwhen supports transfers. Open
        your confirmation email and look for the transfer option. You can move to any available future slot. This is a
        much better option than cancelling and losing your spot, especially if the session is sold out.
      </p>
      <p>Transfers are available once per booking. If you need help with this, reach out and we will walk you through it.</p>

      <h3 class="pt-2 font-serif text-xl text-forest">Why no refunds?</h3>
      <p>
        We keep our pricing accessible because we run lean. Every session fee goes directly toward the course, the
        cart, league activities, and making Monday nights something worth showing up for. When a spot goes unfilled at
        the last minute, that cost is absorbed. There is no way to recover it.
      </p>
      <p>
        This is standard practice across golf leagues. We appreciate your understanding and your commitment to the
        league.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 pb-24">
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-forest/10 bg-blush/10 p-7 text-center reveal">
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate">
        Questions? Reach us at
        <a href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`} class="font-medium text-rose underline-offset-4 hover:underline">{EMAIL}</a>.
        Book your spot at
        <a href={BOOKWHEN_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-medium text-rose underline-offset-4 hover:underline">bookwhen.com/ladiesonthelinks</a>
        and <a href="/register" class="font-medium text-rose underline-offset-4 hover:underline">register</a> so you
        never miss a tee-time release.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
